{
  "texts": [
    "This is where RAG steps in to enhance the accuracy and factual reliability of LLMs.",
    "RAG is an advanced approach that integrates information retrieval systems with LLMs to enhance their accuracy and relevance (Lewis et al., 2020; Li, Su, Cai, Wang & Liu, 2022).",
    "RAG models combine the generative capabilities of LLMs with external knowledge sources, such as databases or document collections, enabling the model to pull real-time information rather than relying solely on pretrained data.",
    "This mechanism addresses the limitations of LLMs, such as hallucinations and outdated knowledge, by grounding generated responses in retrieved, factual data.",
    "A flowchart illustrating the architecture of a RAG model, detailing the interaction between the retrieval and generation components, is shown in Figure 7."
  ]
}